title: Shenzhou-8 spacecraft separates from carrier rocket
description: A modified model of the Long March CZ-2F rocket carrying the unmanned spacecraft Shenzhou-8 blasts off from the launch pad at the Jiuquan Satellite Launch Center in northwest China's Gansu Province， Nov. 1， 2011. (Xinhua/Li Gang)
cleanContent: A modified model of the Long March CZ-2F rocket carrying the unmanned spacecraft Shenzhou-8 blasts off from the launch pad at the Jiuquan Satellite Launch Center in northwest China's Gansu Province, Nov. 1, 2011. (Xinhua/Li Gang)JIUQUAN, Nov. 1 (Xinhua) -- The Shenzhou-8 spacecraft successfully separated from its carrier rocket, a modified Long March-2F, at a height of about 200 km above the Earth.
